race.comment: TEN CARAT LUCY (10) resumes and is a progressive galloper who won and placed here at her first two starts when heavily supported. Will be naturally improved and it's hard to risk the potent Wiggins-Taylor linkage. She can take this out and go on to better things. PANIGALE (2) has switched from the Taylor yard and has been freshened 49 days. He would be right in it if he found anything like his best Victorian form. Has some gear changes and will run along from the inside gate. We may see more from him. RUM RUMBLE (7) is third-up with more to give. Gave away a big start at Mackay 37 days ago in a 55 as a $2.0 favourite and wasn't far away. Tumbles in weight and will push forward. He's well in the mix. FOUR LEAF WONDER (6) led and spiked his figures when missing a nose in a 55 at Emerald. Draws low and has some weight relief. The shorter sprint should advantage.
